name: Kelly's resturaunt

name: Double Tree Motel

name: JC Penney Furniture Outlet
directions: Restrooms are through a narrow hallway to the left of the counter. There are two gendered restrooms, each with two stalls, and one unisex "family" restroom.
comment: Store is very low traffic, with staff mostly in the back. Restrooms have a sharps container available

name: Starbucks Coffee Company
comment: All company owned Starbucks stores have gender neutral bathrooms! :)

name: Blackbird Kitchen  & other businesses in building
Freed Bodyworks
directions: First floor. Will probably need to knock/ring doorbell for admittance because it is a wellness center with a door code.
comment: Typically restrooms are used by clients but anyone in need can come on in. It is an expressly trans- & GNC-accommodating business.

name: Wheelock College Campus Center and Student Residence
directions: First floor, down little "hallway" between computers and school store; on your left

name: Bedlam Lowertown
directions: near the rear entrance.
comment: Everyone is loving and awesome.

name: Tampa International Airport (TPA), 4100 George J Bean Parkway, Tampa, FL 33607, USA
directions: At the Marriot hotel behind the bar in the lobby, follow the hallway on the left towards the pool. Family bathroom is on the right. There are also gender neutral family restrooms in the red baggage claim and the red terminal.
comment: Very safe and anyone can use it. Clean and very nice.

name: World Market
directions: Back right corner

name: Johnson & Wales University Wales Hall
directions: First floor across from Student Employment Office
comment: JWU buildings require card access - must be JWU student, faculty, staff, or guest to access building.

name: 인권중심 사람
directions: first floor

name: The Lunch Room
directions: Both of the restrooms are gender neutral. Walk in the entrance and turn left immediately and walk down the hall. The first restroom on the right. The restroom at the end is not accessible.
comment: The Lunch Room welcomes everyone of all gender expressions. The restrooms are available for use regardless if you are a customer that day or not.

name: Target
directions: Near customer service, directly to the right when you enter. It's a "family restroom".

name: Medley Centre, 500 Medley Centre Parkway, Rochester, NY 14622, USA
directions: When you walk into Target it's to the left before the gendered bathrooms.

name: EAT
directions: One accessible unisex toilet and two individual unisex toilets (i.e. with sinks) off common corridor entered to the right of the counter.
comment: Paying customers only

name: Osol Residence Hall
directions: First floor of Osol Residence Hall has two single occupancy, all-genders bathrooms
comment: You have to be a resident or guest of Osol Residence Hall in order to use these bathrooms.

name: Wilson Residence Hall
directions: Each residential floor has a single occupancy bathrooms with all-genders signage on each side of floor
comment: You have to be a resident or guest of Wilson Residence Hall to use these bathrooms

name: Goodman Residence Hall
directions: Both wings on each floor have single-occupancy bathrooms labeled with all-genders bathroom signs.  The first floor is accessible by wheelchair.
comment: You have to be a resident or guest of Goodman Residence Hall to use these bathrooms

name: Tufts University, Olin Center
directions: 2nd floor has three single occupancy bathrooms. One is marked male, one female, and one unisex and handicapped-accessible. All three are near the elevator (at the south end of the building).
comment: University academic building, so it's usually only open on weekdays and you'll get some curious looks if you don't act as if you belong on campus. You don't need to look undergraduate aged, though. There are faculty and grad students around too. No need to show college ID or anything.

name: Fusion Dance Project
directions: Down the first staircase right, in the hallway
comment: You can't just wander in because there are a lot of children and we're very protective of them. Talk to someone at the front desk and they'll probably let you go.

name: The Vitamin Shoppe
directions: Back of store behind exit door
comment: Management is queer/accepting. Restrooms are behind a door and not visible from sales floor or breakroom.

name: Beer Bunker
directions: In the back near the patio
comment: paying customer but queer owners, I think. Beware: sports atmosphere but people are nice

name: lickety split
directions: Two single user bathrooms in the back.

name: Amazing Grace Antiques
directions: Toward the back of the store, by the kitchen, across from the steps going downstairs.
comment:
When you walk in they'll stop you and ask if you've been there before. If you say yes, they won't give you any trouble. If you say no, they'll just explain about the store a bit. So if you're curious, just do that. 
The bathroom is just its own room, a single stall.

name: The Blind Pig Brewery
comment: Located directly opposite of the gendered restrooms. Tends to be much cleaner and nicer than the gendered rooms anyway. ;)

name: Bailey's Range
comment: They have four single-stall bathrooms total, and each one is explicitly marked as gender-neutral. Of those four, only one is wheelchair accessible and it doubles as the family/changing room. The setup is a little strange in that the sinks are not located within the stalls but directly outside for the other three bathrooms. If you need to use the sink in privacy, you'll need to use the wheelchair accessible room.

name: 12900 Challenger Parkway, Orlando, FL 32826, USA
directions: From the main entrance, take a left and go to the cafeteria. The bathroom is by the vending machines and easy to miss.
comment: Available to students, staff, and registered visitors.

name: Massage Envy
comment: for paying customers

name: Seattle Coffee Works
comment: You need a key :)

name: Family support center of south sound
directions: Just ask front desk. Support services available. Family and lgbtq friendly. You will be asked to sign a confidentiality waiver to protect those seeking services as it is a safe place for all. Sex offenders and perpetrators of domestic violence are not allowed in the center.

name: Memorial Hermann Hospital tower
directions: 5th-7th floors public restrooms are unisex private

name: Village Trough Restaurt
directions: Door to the right of the front counter.
comment: Lots of progressive folks who are friendly and welcoming. Including a gender neutral bathroom was a priority for them.

name: Starbucks Toco Hills
directions: Back of store
comment: you can just go in. Very clean

name: Mongolian Grill
directions: Hall of single stalls next to salad bar.

name: Oshawa Public Library - McLaughlin Branch
directions: 2 single stalls on main floor. At least the one by main entrance is wheelchair accessible. Ask staff for any directions.

name: Art Center College of Design
directions: Very close to the student dining area. On the side of the campus opposite of the big parking lot
comment: Two unisex stalls

name: The Blacksheep Coffee Bar
directions: Off patio in the back
comment: LGBTQ-friendly business. Great coffee. Climber/boulderer hangout.

name: First Congregational Church, United Church of Christ
directions: In west doors, across wooden floor labyrinth, straight down long hallway, just to left of stairs. 2 gender-neutral and accessible restrooms. This church is a safe place for all, regardless of gender identity or sexual orientation.
comment: Doors typically open during regular business hours, 9am - 4pm Monday thru Friday and Sunday mornings between 7:30 and Noon.

name: CB1
directions: Go down the stairs at the back of the cafe.

name: Costa Coffee
directions: At the back of the shop.

name: Costa Coffee
directions: At the back of the shop.

name: First Parish Church - Unitarian Universalist
directions: Follow signs for the church office. Rest rooms are located next to the office.
comment: Rest rooms are available during regular business hours: Tuesday thru Thursday 9:00 am to 1:00 pm, and 9am to 12:00 pm on Fridays.  Church Office is open early September through mid-June.

name: Indy Reads Books
directions: In the back of the store.

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back next to the counter where they hand out drinks.
comment: Don't think you have to be a paying customer, but you do have to ask someone for a key/code.

name: Riverwest Public House Cooperative
directions: When you walk into the bar, there are two bathrooms on the right side. The bathroom with the sign that reads "Sit" has a sit down toilet.  The other bathroom's sign reads "Sit / Stand" and you can choose between a toilet and a urinal. The second bathroom has a small division between the toilet and urinal but no door for privacy.  The signs are very intentionally not gender specific.
comment: The Riverwest Public House Cooperative has "Safe Space" signs posted around the bar. But because it is a bar, you must be 21 or older to go in, unless you're accompanied by a guardian. They have a wheelchair ramp for a side door but you need to call ahead so the staff can set it up. Please note: the bathrooms are not wheelchair accessible.

name: Douglass Dining Hall
directions: Second floor, right of the bridge entrance

name: 17 Highland Street, Plymouth, NH 03264, USA
directions: Bottom floor in the back

name: Hu Hot

comment: Labeled as a "family restroom"

name: 352-394 Park Boulevard, San Diego, CA 92101, USA

name: Wood bridge Mall
street: 153 Woodbridge Center Drive, Woodbridge, NJ 07095, USA

name: jimmy johns
directions: Back of restaurant
comment: you do not have to be a paying customer. Walk way to the back is slightly narrow, may have trouble moving a wheelchair to the back.

name: Speedway
directions: Towards the back, partially concealed by a short hallway
comment:
Staff is very trans-friendly and no purchase is necessary to use the facilities. 
Facilities would be difficult, though, for someone using larger mobility assistance, as the doors are of average width and on a hallway.

name: Piedmont High School
directions: It is in the thirties building. If you enter through the rightmost door and walk to the last classroom on the right side the next door is the gender neutral restroom
comment: Only open during school hours/about an hour before and after. Best to be a PHS student or visiting sports team member.

name: Baked & Wired
directions: All the way in the back left of the store, past the wall of napkins

name: Bangor Public Library
